3 Steps to grow your clientele as a hairstylist 💇🏽‍♀️

1. Niche down. What type of stylist are you? Are you a braider? A natural hair care specialist? an extension specialist? Hair growth expert? You may be good at all of these things but the best way to build your clientele is by choosing one category to specialize in AND then niche down even more and choose one style to specialize in as well. This is not to say you cannot do other styles, but become the GO TO for a specific hairstyle and once you get people in you can inform them of the other services you offer.

2. CONTENT CONTENT CONTENT. Record everything, even if it turns out not so great to post, learn from what you record. Learn lighting, learn camera settings, learn angles, and RECORD. If it makes it easier you can find hair videos for inspiration and use them as a guide on what angles and lighting to use. When choosing inspo videos make sure you choose videos that have high engagement. (Do not steal content, but using videos as a guide on how to create your own will help you as you get better with content).

3. Use hashtags. Pay for ads. Collaborate with influencers. All of these things will increase your reach and attract new followers. As the followers begin to come in DM them and introduce yourself, your current deals/specials and ask them open ended questions such as “do you have your next hairstyle in mind yet? If so what is it? 😍” to leave room for responses! Be genuine in your approach, analyze what does and does not work and adjust if/when necessary! People hate to be sold to, make it more about an experience vs a pitch.

3 WAYS TO INCREASE YOUR INCOME:
1. Start providing the hair for installs such as quick weaves, sew ins and even boho curls for knotless. The clients have to get the hair from somewhere, why not offer it yourself?! 😉

2. Start a product line that aligns with your signature service. A braider could sell edge control, Hair oils, braid spray ect, a ponytail gurú could sell a ponytail molding spray, an extension specialist should most definitely be selling extensions as mentioned above as well as a dry shampoo formula!

3. Offer add on services such as: a shampoo if not already included, steam treatment, braid take down, ect. Most people will add these services on when they know they are available because they don’t want to do them at home!

Increasing your income as a hairstylist isn’t as hard as we make it seem. Don’t overthink it! Just add one thing at a time, and before you know it your new products/service add ins will be adding up! 🖤

The work doesn’t stop when the clients leave! It’s the work you put in AFTER they leave that sets you up for life!

Here are 5 things you as a beauty professional should be doing to plan for your future:
1. Invest in multiple life insurance policies! Yes this will be for your family when you pass but also there are some policies that allow you to take money out of in the future, it acts as a safe investment plan for future purchases such as opening your own salon, purchasing a house, buying a boat 😂 ect. 

2. Create streams of passive income that relate to your business, a product line, digital products, ect. Something that makes money when you’re asleep. It doesn’t have to make $1M on your first drop for it to be successful! Take your time, and perfect your marketing strategy, consistency will begin to yield results! But you have to START!

3. THINK BIG! Thinking small is easy, it’s comfortable, and it’s safe. None of those things have ever made an extraordinary person successful! If you want to be average, think small, but if you want to be EXTRAORDINARY then you have to think BIGGER! It starts in the mind. It starts in your belief system, what you believe is what you receive. Always.

4. Find someone that you look up to, and study them! If you can have them as a mentor that’s great, but if you cannot, study them! Their work ethic, their mindset, ect. You HAVE to have someone you look up to in order to see exactly what you want manifest in their life, because it will then prove to you that it’s possible for you as well.

5. LOCK IN. Get serious. get consistent. Get DISCIPLINED and get real with yourself about where you are vs where you want to be, then figure out what you have to do to close that gap!

You have to make yourself VALUABLE! High paying clients want an entire experience, not just the service. 

Here’s some tips on how you can make yourself valuable as a beauty professional:

1. Offer exceptional communication and customer service. As beauty pro’s we work with our hands so sometimes it’s hard to respond to our clients as soon as they reach out to us, to avoid long response times you can schedule 2 times out of your day where you respond to all messages, in the morning and at night. It’s best to set an alarm to ensure you don’t forget. Also, you can offer consultations for services that require clients to have longer more engaging conversations. These consultations can be paid or free.

2. Keep a CLEAN environment. I understand that we have busy days, and it’s normal for you to have a few things placed incorrectly after taking a couple clients, but if you have to, schedule in 5 minutes of tidying before and after each client to ensure that when your clients come in they feel like they are in a clean and comfortable environment.

3. Learn how to read people. Every client is NOT the same. You have your turnt up clients that are with the vibes, and you have your lowkey clients that like a more calm environment. Learn how to read your clients and cater the experience to them specifically so they are comfortable coming back to you!

These 3 tips will set you apart and have your clients ready to book their next appointments before they leave your chair! 💅🏽
